paragraphs.text: The Expression Editor is used across various nodes such as Derived Variable, Filter, Select, and Fill. It is utilized to create new calculated values or to edit expressions for conditions. Users can edit expressions entirely through mouse operations, or, once they become familiar with the interface, they can type directly into the expression input window for faster editing.

rows.text: ToolbarProvides expression editing features such as Undo/Redo, Find, and Bookmark in a toolbar format for convenient access.

Expression Editing WindowThis is where expressions are edited. Users can enter expressions manually or use tools (4) ~ (8) to edit them. By using these tools, expressions used in ECMiner™ can be easily edited through mouse operations.

Available VariablesDisplays the list of existing variables available in the current node. Select the variable you wish to use and double-click it to add it to the editing window. When added, it appears enclosed in curly braces (e.g., {DATE}), indicating that it represents a variable.
IF StatementClicking the IF Statement button to insert the IF ~ THEN ~ ELSE ~ ENDIF statement into the expression.
Edit ToolClick the Edit Tool button to open the function category panel on the right.

Function CategoryAllows users to choose from the provided function categories, including Transformation, Math/Trigonometric, Text, Date/Time, Variable Statistics, and Information functions. When the category is changed, the list of corresponding functions appears in section (4).

Function List Displays functions belonging to the selected function category. To insert a function, double-click or press the Add button to insert it into the Expression Editing Window. The usage and a brief description of the selected function appear in section (8).
Function DescriptionDisplays a brief description and usage information of the currently selected function.

Numeric and Symbol ButtonsProvides frequently used numbers and symbols as buttons for quick editing using mouse operations. Clicking a button inserts the corresponding number or symbol into the editing window.
Syntax CheckChecks whether the current expression syntax is valid. If an error is detected, an error message is displayed, allowing users to identify and correct the mistake.

Saving and Loading Expressions You can save the current expression or open a previously saved one for reuse. Clicking the Clear button deletes all expressions currently entered. The file extension for the expressions is *.eaf

Confirm or Cancel Applies or cancels the current expression input. Clicking the OK button enters the expression after performing syntax validation.If an invalid expression is entered, the program may not function properly.
